  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0d9c \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dad\u0db8\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9c\u0d82 \u0dc0\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb \u0d85\u0db1\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0d87\u0d9f\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A flood warning from the Irrigation Department",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Irrigation Department has issued an early flood warning notice saying that if heavy rains occur in the future, there may be a risk of flooding along certain rivers.",
        "According to the forecasts of the Department of Meteorology, heavy rains may occur in some areas tonight (5) and tomorrow (6) as well, so the Irrigation Department states that there may be a flood situation in one or more of the Atthanagalu, Kalu, Kelani, Ging and Nilwala river basins.",
        "Director of Irrigation (Hydrology and Disaster Management) Engineer SPC Sugeeshwara said that heavy water flow may occur in those river basins and tributaries and the people living nearby should be aware of possible flood situations tonight (5) and in the next few days. said.",
        "Mr. Sugeeshwara also said that care should be taken in activities such as boating, swimming, and crossing the rivers and tributaries."
      ],
